## Authorize via fingerprint ##

* use fingerprint for login, sudo, etc
* use password as fallback

Install libfprint,fprintd

Modify /etc/pam.d/system-auth :

# Begin /etc/pam.d/system-auth

################fingerprint#############
auth       required     pam_env.so
auth       sufficient   pam_fprintd.so
auth       sufficient   pam_unix.so try_first_pass likeauth nullok
auth       required     pam_deny.so
##########################################

#auth      required    pam_unix.so

# End /etc/pam.d/system-auth

Users should be in groups input & plugdev to access fingerprint reader
